---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">About Me</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    A passionate electrical engineer with expertise in computer science, AI, and hardware systems, backed by combined 3+ years of full-time and working student experiences at BOSCH, MAHLE, and TCS. Skilled in embedded software development (C programming), hardware validation, and dynamic system modeling using MATLAB/Simulink, with a strong aptitude for problem-solving and cross-functional collaboration.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Embedded Software Developer (Working Student)"
      subtitle="Aug 2024 – Jan 2025 at Robert Bosch GmbH, Stuttgart, Germany"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6">
        <li>Supported software development of vehicle access systems (BLE/UWB).</li>
        <li>Validated third-party software components for AUTOSAR-based platforms.</li>
        <li>Enhanced hardware abstraction layer reliability through microcontroller testing and integrated UWB MAC (CCC standards) via HiL testing.</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="System Validation for Inductive Charging of EVs (Internship)"
      subtitle="Oct 2023 – Mar 2024 at Mahle International GmbH, Stuttgart, Germany"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6">
        <li>Analyzed system measurements (MATLAB) and led presentations to the SAE team for WPT positioning (SAE J2954).</li>
        <li>Reduced manual testing hours by 30% by restructuring automated test sequences.</li>
        <li>Enhanced validation using C programming for signal processing and implementing CAN communication.</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Engineering Development - Deep Learning Loop (Working Student)"
      subtitle="Nov 2022 – Oct 2023 at Robert Bosch GmbH, Stuttgart, Germany"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6">
        <li>Generated ground truth for ADAS by developing data selection strategies.</li>
        <li>Reduced validation errors by guiding an international team in the development process.</li>
        <li>Enhanced processing accuracy and reduced processing time by 35% by implementing Python scripts for handling large XML/Excel files.</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Assistant Systems Engineer - Informatica Developer"
      subtitle="Oct 2020 – Feb 2022 at TATA Consultancy Services (TCS), Bangalore, India"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6">
        <li>Enhanced data extraction efficiency by 15% by developing and testing Informatica ETL jobs.</li>
        <li>Increased data processing efficiency by scheduling and automating workflows (Control M, Unix shell scripting).</li>
        <li>Streamlined code deployment using Git, following agile methodology.</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Master of Science in Electrical Engineering (Smart Systems)"
      subtitle="2022 – Present at University of Stuttgart, Germany"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6">
        <li><b>Master Thesis:</b> Embedded Real-Time Identification of Coupling Factor for Inductive Power Transfer Systems.</li>
        <li><b>Research Thesis:</b> Industrial automation project with micro-services and virtual knowledge graphs.</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor of Technology (Honors) in Electrical & Electronics Engineering"
      subtitle="2016 – 2020 at Government Engineering College, Thrissur, India"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6">
        <li><b>CGPA:</b> 8.44/10 (Awarded honors degree)</li>
        <li><b>Thesis:</b> A Vision Based Approach for Control of Robotic Arm for Pick and Place Application.</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.coursera.org/specializations/deep-learning" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Deep Learning (Specialization) from Coursera by deeplearning.ai
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.coursera.org/professional-certificates/google-it-automation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Google IT Automation with Python (Professional Certification)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.edx.org/course/image-processing-and-analysis-for-life-scientists" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Image Processing and Analysis for Life Scientists, EPFLx
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span>Blockchain Architecture Design and Use Cases, IIT Kharagpur & IBM Research</span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Core Competencies</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-4">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Programming Languages</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc md:columns-3 columns-2 mx-6">
      <li>Python</li>
      <li>C</li>
      <li>MATLAB</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-4">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Tools & Technologies</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc md:columns-3 columns-2 mx-6">
      <li>SQL</li>
      <li>NoSQL</li>
      <li>PLECS</li>
      <li>TensorFlow & Keras</li>
      <li>Informatica</li>
      <li>Data Analysis</li>
      <li>Docker</li>
      <li>Kubernetes</li>
      <li>AWS</li>
      <li>Raspberry Pi</li>
      <li>Linux</li>
      <li>CAN</li>
      <li>Git</li>
      <li>Knowledge Graphs</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Soft Skills</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc md:columns-3 columns-2 mx-6">
      <li>Attention to detail</li>
      <li>Innovative thinking</li>
      <li>Teamwork & Leadership</li>
      <li>Analytical & Independent</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>